description: Creates a customer profile. You can have up to five customer profiles, each representing a distinct private network. A profile is the mechanism used to create the concept of a private network.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: Specifies the name of the profile.

parameters.name: phone
parameters.description: Specifies the phone number associated with the profile.

parameters.name: businessName
parameters.description: Specifies the name for the business associated with this profile.

parameters.name: logging
parameters.description: Specifies whether or not logging is enabled for this profile.

parameters.name: clientToken
parameters.description: Reserved for future use. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

parameters.name: tags
parameters.description: Specifies the key-value pairs assigned to ARNs that you can use to group and search for resources by type. You can attach this metadata to resources (capabilities, partnerships, and so on) for any purpose. (dict) --- Creates a key-value pair for a specific resource. Tags are metadata that you can use to search for and group a resource for various purposes. You can apply tags to capabilities, partnerships, profiles and transformers. A tag key can take more than one value. For example, to group capabilities for accounting purposes, you might create a tag called Group and assign the values Research and Accounting to that group. Specifies the name assigned to the tag that you create. Contains one or more values that you assigned to the key name that you create.

nested_params.name: Key
nested_params.description: Specifies the name assigned to the tag that you create.

nested_params.name: Value
nested_params.description: Contains one or more values that you assigned to the key name that you create.

nested_items.name: profileId
nested_items.description: Returns the unique, system-generated identifier for the profile.

nested_items.name: profileArn
nested_items.description: Returns an Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the profile.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: Returns the name of the profile, used to identify it.

nested_items.name: businessName
nested_items.description: Returns the name for the business associated with this profile.

nested_items.name: phone
nested_items.description: Returns the phone number associated with the profile.

nested_items.name: email
nested_items.description: Returns the email address associated with this customer profile.

nested_items.name: logging
nested_items.description: Returns whether or not logging is turned on for this profile.

nested_items.name: logGroupName
nested_items.description: Returns the name of the logging group.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: Returns a timestamp representing the time the profile was created.
